Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced). Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons.

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp}, half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1/2%tbsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{14-16%minutes}. Loosely cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

Once water is boiling, add @gemelli pasta{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 1/2 cups pasta cooking water (2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add @Italian chicken sausage{9%oz} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned all over, ~{3-4%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Add @tomato paste{1.5%oz} and remaining @Tuscan Heat Spice{1/2%tbsp} to pan. Cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1 cup reserved pasta cooking water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of salt and pepper. Bring to a low simmer; cook until sauce is slightly thickened and sausage is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Reduce heat under pan to medium low.

Stir gemelli, zucchini, @sour cream{2%tbsp}, and @butter{1%tbsp} into pan until thoroughly combined.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide between bowls. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}.